The paper deals with the security of code-based cryptosystems, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also involves decoding algorithms and complexity analysis, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of quantum search and quantum walk techniques suggests a connection to quantum computing (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents an improvement to an existing algorithm, which could be considered a machine learning or optimization problem (cs.LG).
